procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic analysis and clinical laboratory safety assessments

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: 12-Lead Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECGs extracted from Holter recordings at multiple timepoints for cardiac repolarization assessment

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads

procedures.name: Holter Monitoring
procedures.label: Holter Recording
procedures.description: Continuous Holter recordings starting 1 hour prior to first timepoint on Day 1 and lasting at least until 24 hours postdose

code.decode: External electrocardiographic recording up to 48 hours

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: Complete physical examination at screening and brief examination on Days -1 of each period to recheck eligibility and healthy state

procedures.name: Vital Signs Assessment
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of vital signs including body temperature on Day -1 of each period and on dosing days at predose and 1, 2, 6, and 24 h postdose

procedures.name: Serum Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Serum pregnancy test performed at screening and Day -1 of each treatment period

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Tests
procedures.label: Lab Tests
procedures.description: Blood samples for clinical laboratory safety assessments collected in fasted condition including hematology, biochemistry, and urinalysis

procedures.name: Viral Serology Testing
procedures.label: Viral Serology
procedures.description: Testing for hepatitis B surface antigen, hepatitis B core antibody, hepatitis C antibody, and HIV I and II

procedures.name: QuantiFERON Test
procedures.label: TB Test
procedures.description: QuantiFERON test for tuberculosis screening within 4 weeks prior to or at the time of Screening

code.decode: Tuberculosis test, cell mediated immunity antigen response measurement

procedures.name: SARS-CoV-2 Testing
procedures.label: COVID-19 Test
procedures.description: SARS-CoV-2 testing at Screening and Study Day -1

code.decode: Infectious agent detection by nucleic acid, SARS-CoV-2

procedures.name: Drugs of Abuse Screening
procedures.label: Drug Screen
procedures.description: Testing for cotinine, alcohol and drugs of abuse at Screening and Day -1

procedures.name: Estimated Glomerular Filtration Rate
procedures.label: eGFR
procedures.description: eGFR assessment at screening for renal function evaluation

procedures.name: Oral Drug Administration
procedures.label: Study Drug Dosing
procedures.description: Single oral dose administration of study intervention under fasted conditions on Day 1 of each treatment period

procedures.name: Pharmacokinetic Blood Sampling
procedures.label: PK Sampling
procedures.description: Plasma samples for PK analysis collected at predose and 15, 30 min, and 1, 1.5, 2, 2.5, 3, 4, 6, 8, 12, 16 and 24 h postdose

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

medicalDevices.name: Holter Monitor
medicalDevices.label: Holter ECG Device
medicalDevices.description: Continuous electrocardiographic recording device for extracting triplicate 12-lead ECGs at specified timepoints

medicalDevices.name: 12-Lead ECG Device
medicalDevices.label: Safety ECG
medicalDevices.description: Standard 12-lead electrocardiogram device for safety ECG assessments

medicalDevices.name: ECG Electrodes
medicalDevices.label: ECG Electrodes
medicalDevices.description: Electrodes used for ECG procedures; participants with contact allergies to ECG electrodes are excluded
